Exercice:
Write two functions; 
the first one takes a string as argument and returns toInt("5") ➞ 5
the second function takes a number as argument and returns toStr(100) ➞ "100"
function toInt(str) { 
  return parseInt(str) 
}
function toStr(num){
  return num.toString();
}
console.log(toInt("123"));
console.log(toStr(9562));
