Exercice:
Create a function that takes a character as argument then returns its ASCII value.
("A") ➞ 65
("m") ➞ 109
("\") ➞ 92

function ConvertToAsci(variable) {
return variable.charCodeAt(2);
}
console.log(ConvertToAsci("AB"));
